import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='year', y='miles', bins=20, legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Miles Driven', loc='upper left')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='gas', y='gas_per_mile')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between gas prices and gas consumption per mile?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Gas Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Consumption per Mile')
    plt.legend(title='Gas Prices vs Gas Consumption per Mile', loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='gas_per_mile', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['gas_per_mile'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['gas_per_mile'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Gas Consumption per Mile')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of gas consumption per mile?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
